## Problem
ViewMode is currently a string union type:
```typescript
export type ViewMode = "list" | "kanban" | "timeline";
```

While correct, an enum with descriptions would be more AI-friendly.

## Solution
```typescript
/**
 * Project view modes available in TickTick.
 */
export enum ViewMode {
  /** Traditional list view - tasks in a vertical list */
  List = 'list',
  /** Kanban board view - tasks in columns by status */
  Kanban = 'kanban',
  /** Timeline/Gantt view - tasks on a calendar timeline */
  Timeline = 'timeline',
}
```

## Problem
Current Status enum uses magic numbers that are hard for AI to understand:
```typescript
export enum Status {
  Normal = 0,
  Completed = 1,  // Also wrong value for Task!
}
```

## Solution
Create descriptive, AI-friendly enums:
```typescript
export enum TaskStatus {
  /** Task is active and not yet completed */
  Active = 0,
  /** Task has been completed */
  Completed = 2,
}

export enum ChecklistItemStatus {
  /** Subtask is unchecked/incomplete */
  Unchecked = 0,
  /** Subtask is checked/complete */
  Checked = 1,
}
```

Use clear names that communicate intent without needing comments.

## Problem
ProjectKind is currently a string union type:
```typescript
export type ProjectKind = "TASK" | "NOTE";
```

## Solution
```typescript
/**
 * Types of projects in TickTick.
 */
export enum ProjectKind {
  /** Standard task list project */
  Task = 'TASK',
  /** Note-taking project */
  Note = 'NOTE',
}
```
